--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party build-time dependencies (not redistributed)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

* The LLVM Project (https://llvm.org/)

  CAST's JIT code generation uses LLVM (ORC JIT for CPU, NVPTX for
  CUDA) via C++ FFI. CAST links against the system LLVM libraries at
  build time; no LLVM source or binary is included in this repository.
  LLVM is distributed under the Apache License 2.0 with LLVM Exceptions
  (https://llvm.org/LICENSE.txt).

* NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit (https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-toolkit)

  The optional `cuda` feature links against libcuda and libnvJitLink at
  build time. CUDA is distributed by NVIDIA under its own license terms;
  no CUDA source or binary is included in this repository.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party code vendored in this repository (not part of the cast crate)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

The `external/` directory contains third-party assets used for
benchmarking and reference only. These are NOT part of the compiled
`cast` library and retain their original licenses.

* external/NWQ-Sim/

  NWQ-Sim, an HPC quantum-circuit simulator by Ang Li et al. (Pacific
  Northwest National Laboratory), vendored for head-to-head benchmarking
  against CAST. Distributed under the MIT License. See
  external/NWQ-Sim/LICENSE and external/NWQ-Sim/NOTICE for details.

* external/DAC25__Quantum_Simulation.pdf
* external/Quantum_Circuit_Simulation_Journal.pdf

  Preprint and journal submission PDFs of CAST papers, included for
  reference when evaluating the simulator's results.
